<p>
  <span class="nym">Adiel</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Hebrew</span> <i>עדיאל</i> 'ornament of God'
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a handful of obsure Old Testament characters. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Adiel</i>. Geneva Bible (1560): <i>Adiél</i>; (1587): <i>Adiel</i>. Sagradas Escrituras (1569): <i>Adiel</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This name came into use in England in the second half of the 16th C.</p>
  
  


<dl>
<dt><span class="area">England</span></dt>
<dd>
<dl>
<dt><span class="lang">Early Modern English</span></dt>
